snippet.textDisplay:
48mp 1/1.3" sensor is much better for video recording.
in 4k mode it uses 32mp with pixel binning ( 32/4 = 8 ) (66.7% of sensor )
in 8k mode it uses 32mp again, but without pixel binning. (66.7% of sensor )
so fov will be same in 4k and 8k mode.
also quality will be higher because of bigger pixels. ( in 8k mode from 0.8 micron to 1.2 micron)
that 108mp sensor was not a wise move !
in 4k recording it uses 72mp with pixel binning (72/9=8) (66.7% of sensor)
in 8k recording it uses only 32mp without pixel binning ( 29.6% of sensor ) so that cropping happens compared to 4k recording.

snippet.textDisplay:
Sorry, but whoever makes a statement like: "I zoom with my feet" instantly loses all credibility as a photographer. Ever wondered why portrait lenses are telephoto lenses? It's because the distance gives a better compression of the subject. Can you zoom with your feet for a tight headshot? Yes. But then your subject will have a distorted face.

You are used to zooming with your feet because your iphone didnt give you any other option.

Next time you're in the last row of a ball game or concert please try zooming with your feet.
